<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="3b503e0e-963f-5003-bb85-0aad07014178" activityNameId="10631fe2-d141-4f8c-962a-4b24206968de" parentActivityId="c80b2078-9feb-5e4e-821a-385657c3b410" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">sodium pyrophosphate production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Sodium pyrophosphate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">TETRASODIUM PYROPHOSPHATE</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Tetrasodium diphosphate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Phosphotex</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">TSPP</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">7722-88-5</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the delivery of material and energy inputs on site.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of dried sodium pyrophosphate. This dataset includes raw materials, energy uses, infrastructure and emissions (water produced by chemical reaction is assumed released to the air).</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of sodium pyrophosphate. Sodium pyrophosphate is a buffering, dispersing and thickening agent and is also used as a food additive. It is often used in water treatment. Sodium pyrophosphate is produced by the reaction of phosphoric acid with sodium carbonate and then heated.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This dataset is based on stoechiometric calculations as well as approximations based on data from a large chemical plant (Gendorf 2016). It is a rough estimation created for the tap water production dataset.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Reference:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Idealized reaction of sodium carbonate with phosphoric acid to give disodium phosphate, which is then heated to 450°C to give sodium pyrophosphate: </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">2 Na2CO3 + 2 H3PO4 -&gt; 2 Na2HPO4 + 2 CO2 + 2 H2O </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">2 Na2HPO4 -&gt; Na4P2O7 + H2O</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2012-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data in this dataset come from different years, but overall form the most realistic picture of the production. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
